The Quality Assurance Engineer is a smart and passionate engineer, who will work with our engineering team in the development of the world's most technologically advanced inspection and factory control solutions. Nanotronics is making manufacturing fast, accurate and cost-efficient by combining optical and atomic force microscopy with machine learning and artificial intelligence. The solutions we build push the envelope of what can be done, so we need team members, who are highly intelligent, hardworking and creative. The ideal candidate is a self-starter, who work well with in fast-paced, ever-evolving environment. 
The QA Engineer is an intelligent and detail-oriented person, who will create and implement a QA strategy and continually look to improve our testing and deployment strategies. This person will be responsible for ensuring that our software doesnâ€™t get to our customers until it meets the highest standard of quality that our management and product teams set. The QA Engineer will play a critical role in improving quality, speeding up development time, and shipping better products more consistently and the role has a lot of potential for growth. The QA Engineer will focus on documentation and process standardization â€“ documenting software and hardware procedures for the entire assembly of customer tools. 
